# Quality Gates Rule

## Every item must pass ALL 4 gates before release. No exceptions.

---

## Gate 1: PM Validation

Check the backlog item's `## PM Plan` section:

- [ ] Problem is clearly defined (what problem, why it matters)
- [ ] Scope is explicitly limited (what IS in scope)
- [ ] Non-goals are listed (what is OUT of scope)
- [ ] Expected behavior is described with input/output examples
- [ ] SOT section traceability is present

**If any checkbox fails → STOP. Run `/plan-feature` to fix.**

---

## Gate 2: QA Validation

Check the backlog item's `## QA Test Plan` section:

- [ ] At least 2 happy path test cases defined
- [ ] At least 2 edge case test cases defined
- [ ] At least 1 failure case test case defined
- [ ] At least 1 unknown case test case defined (returns `status: "unknown"`)
- [ ] All test cases have explicit input AND expected output
- [ ] Test files exist in `tests/` and are executable

**If any checkbox fails → STOP. Run `/write-tests` to fix.**

---

## Gate 3: Dev Validation

Inspect the source code in `src/`:

- [ ] All functions are pure (no side effects, no mutations)
- [ ] No DOM or browser API usage (`document`, `window`, `navigator`) in engine core
- [ ] No randomness (`Math.random`, `crypto.random`)
- [ ] All types are explicit (no `any`)
- [ ] No external dependencies added without justification
- [ ] Algorithm complexity is O(n) or better
- [ ] Deterministic: same input always produces same output

**If any checkbox fails → STOP. Fix the implementation.**

---

## Gate 4: Test Coverage

Run the test suite and verify:

- [ ] All defined test cases have corresponding test implementations
- [ ] `npx vitest --run` exits with code 0 (all tests pass)
- [ ] No skipped or pending tests
- [ ] Every `src/` file has at least one corresponding test file

**If any checkbox fails → STOP. Fix tests or implementation.**

---

## Running Gates

Gates are checked:
1. **Individually** — each command (`/plan-feature`, `/write-tests`, `/implement`) checks its relevant gate
2. **Collectively** — `/validate` runs ALL 4 gates in sequence
3. **Before release** — `/release` refuses to proceed if `/validate` hasn't passed

## Validation Report Format

After running all gates, append to the backlog item:

```
## Validation Report

Date: YYYY-MM-DD

| Gate | Status | Notes |
|------|--------|-------|
| PM Validation | PASS/FAIL | ... |
| QA Validation | PASS/FAIL | ... |
| Dev Validation | PASS/FAIL | ... |
| Test Coverage | PASS/FAIL | ... |

Overall: PASS/FAIL
```
